---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import FooterComponent from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const usageSnippet = `---
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const legalLinks = [
  { href: '/privacy', label: 'Privacy Policy' },
  { href: '/terms', label: 'Terms of Service' },
  { href: '/cookies', label: 'Cookie Policy' }
];

const socialLinks = [
  { href: 'https://twitter.com/yourproject', label: 'Twitter', external: true },
  { href: 'https://github.com/yourproject', label: 'GitHub', external: true }
];

---

<Footer
  brand="Your Project"
  brandUrl="/"
  legalLinks={legalLinks}
  socialLinks={socialLinks}
  showBrand={true}
  showYear={true}
/>`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Footer"
  description="Accessible site footer with WCAG AAA compliance, flexible layouts, and comprehensive link management."
>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      Footer is a semantic site footer component that provides a clean, accessible way to display
      copyright information, legal links, social media links, and external resources. 
      Built with WCAG AAA compliance in mind, featuring enhanced contrast ratios and comprehensive ARIA support.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      The component offers flexible layouts, responsive design, and semantic HTML structure
      for optimal accessibility and SEO benefits.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
        <dt class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200">brand?</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Brand name to display in the footer. Defaults to <code>"Your Project"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
        <dt class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200">brandUrl?</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          URL to link the brand name to. If provided, brand becomes clickable.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
        <dt class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200">year?</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Copyright year to display. Defaults to current year.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
        <dt class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200">legalLinks?</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Array of legal/policy links. Each link object contains <code>href</code>, <code>label</code>, optional <code>ariaLabel</code> and <code>external</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
        <dt class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200">socialLinks?</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Array of social media links. Same structure as legal links but styled differently.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
        <dt class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200">showBrand?</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Whether to show the brand/copyright section. Defaults to <code>true</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
        <dt class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200">ariaLabel?</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Accessible label for the footer element. Defaults to <code>"Site footer"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm">
        <dt class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200">className?</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Additional CSS classes to apply to the footer element.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Usage</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        Import the Footer component and configure it with your brand information and links.
        The component automatically handles responsive layouts and accessibility.
      </p>
      <pre class="rounded bg-slate-950/50 p-4 text-sm text-slate-300 overflow-x-auto"><code>{usageSnippet}</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Examples</h2>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Simple Footer</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Basic footer with brand name and legal links.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-4">
          <FooterComponent
            brand="Comet Astro"
            legalLinks={[
              { href: '/privacy', label: 'Privacy Policy' },
              { href: '/terms', label: 'Terms of Service' }
            ]}
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Footer with Social Links</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Footer including social media links with proper external link handling.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-4">
          <FooterComponent
            brand="Comet Astro"
            brandUrl="/"
            legalLinks={[
              { href: '/privacy', label: 'Privacy' },
              { href: '/terms', label: 'Terms' }
            ]}
            socialLinks={[
              { href: 'https://twitter.com/comet', label: 'Twitter', external: true },
              { href: 'https://github.com/comet', label: 'GitHub', external: true }
            ]}
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Minimal Footer</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Minimal footer with just brand information.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-4">
          <FooterComponent
            brand="Simple Brand"
            showYear={false}
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
        The Footer component is built with comprehensive accessibility features:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300 list-disc list-inside ml-4">
        <li>Semantic <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code> element with proper <code>role="contentinfo"</code></li>
        <li>Enhanced contrast ratios (7:1+) for WCAG AAA compliance in both light and dark modes</li>
        <li>Proper navigation landmarks with descriptive <code>aria-label</code> attributes</li>
        <li>Screen reader announcements for external links ("opens in new window")</li>
        <li>Focus management with visible focus rings and proper tab order</li>
        <li>Keyboard navigation support for all interactive elements</li>
        <li>Responsive design that maintains accessibility across all device sizes</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/10 p-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-200">
          <strong>Best Practice:</strong> Always provide meaningful <code>ariaLabel</code> values for links
          when the default text isn't descriptive enough. Use the <code>external</code> flag for links
          that open in new windows to ensure proper screen reader announcements.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
